Key Match Events: Cleveland Cavaliers secured a 129-122 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder.
Jarrett Allen and Evan Mobley combined for 46 points and 22 rebounds.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored a game-high 31 points and nine assists.
Isaiah Hartenstein finished two assists shy of a triple-double with 18 points and 11 rebounds.
Darius Garland's clutch basket put the game away for the Cavaliers.
Post-Match Reflections: Cavs coach Kenny Atkinson acknowledged doubts about Cleveland's ability to win this game.
Max Strus made a significant impact with five 3-pointers and five assists off the bench.
The Thunder missed Chet Holmgren's presence in the paint.
The Thunder showed they can survive stretches without Shai Gilgeous-Alexander.
Both teams displayed mastery of their systems, with the third quarter being particularly splendid.
Others: The teams will meet again on January 16 in Oklahoma City.
The Cavaliers' win streak extended to 11 games.
The Thunder's 15-game win streak was snapped.
